Aviva plc Key Developments

Aviva to Cut 120 Jobs Following Office Closure
Jul 13 17
Aviva has announced the closure of its Southend office and a reduction of staff in its claims field team, resulting in 120 job losses. Aviva will cut 120 jobs as part of plans to close its office in Southend. The company is proposing that work carried out in its Southend-based commercial property business will move to Perth, where its property claims operations are based. As a result, Aviva will close its Southend office by the end of May 2018, at the expense of 86 jobs. The firm is also reducing the number of staff in its claims field team due to new technology.


Aviva plc Appoints Maurice Tulloch as an Executive Director
Jun 21 17
Aviva plc has appointed Mr. Maurice Tulloch as an Executive Director of the Company with effect from 20 June 2017. Maurice is currently Chief Executive Officer, International Insurance, with responsibility for Aviva's insurance operations in France, Canada, Ireland, Spain, Italy, Poland, Turkey and India.


Aviva Seeks Acquisitions
May 24 17
Aviva plc (LSE:AV.) is seeking acquisitions in 'insurtech', artificial intelligence, but nothing is imminent.


